Description: The Kaiko Reference Data Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API. Successful responses show code (btc), name (bitcoin), assets class (cryptocurrency, and asset classes (cryptocurrency).
The Kaiko Reference Data Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to retrieve data from assets, exhanges, and instruments. Authentication is not required.

The Channelize Android Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to integrate broadcast messages, smart push notifications, media-rich conversations, high-quality video and voice calling, and one to one group conversations.

The Channelize iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to interact with the API to implement smart push notifications, quote and reply messages, typing indicator, delivery and read receipts, rich URL previews, and integration support for external chatbots using DialogFlow and Amazon Lex.

The Channelize JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to initialize, configure, and build a chat. Functionalities include one to one group conversations, video and voice calling, media-rich conversations, and smart push notifications.

This Go example demonstrates how to retrieve transaction status. The test application creates a sender account, creates a client, creates a transfer transaction, sends a transaction, and gets the status.
This Go Sample Code demonstrates how to create a sender account, create a client, deploy a contract, and create a client query using a public key and contract name.
This Go Sample Code demonstrates how to retrieve a block, check if the block contains a call to trigger a contract, and start the signed transactions iterator.
Go example that performs a stress test on the blockchain implementation by posting many transactions while dropping messages.
This Go example demonstrates how to send a transaction to the blockchain using a Token. This commits the transaction and skips invalid ones.
This Go Sample Code tests for memory leaks when sending many transactions and shutting down.
This Go example demonstrates how to perform benchmarks on the consensus implementation. This test application sends a transaction to a block and waits for the validator to acknowledge.
The Modulr Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to create a virtual card, get an account, and get transactions.
The Modulr Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement financial and business features. An API Key is required to authenticate.

The Modulr Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to authenticate the API with an API Key and use POST verbs to make requests to the API. Responses will display financial information to implement into business applications.
This Python example demonstrates how to initialize the validation service. The test application performs asynchronous validations after setup.
Python Sample Code that demonstrates how to retrieve event-based notifications. This also clears events, lists events, and updates webhooks.
This Python Sample Code utilizes the appropriate service to perform merchant-based signing. The application retrieves a transaction by ID, and performs validation using an asynchronous method.
Python example that demonstrates how to validate sessions using the JSON Web Tokens service. This tests the service using threaded processing.
This Python example starts the identification service and gets a specific session. The application performs identification and starts a bank ID mobile session, asynchronously.
This Python example demonstrates admin-related methods. The test application retrieves an account, updates an account, lists account names, lists transactions, and retrieves templates.
This example utilizes the batch service to perform multiple API requests. POST is used to create jobs, and GET to monitor job status.
Category: Mapping, Addresses, Location, Logistics, Optimization, Postcodes, Transportation, Travel, Zip Codes

Description: JavaScript example that demonstrates how to use the batch service to perform multiple calls. This service is based on asynchronous calls. HTTP GET requests are used to monitor job execution, and POST requests to create jobs.
Category: Mapping, Addresses, Location, Logistics, Optimization, Postcodes, Transportation, Travel, Zip Codes

Description: This example uses the node-fetch library to perform multiple API requests using the batch service. This demonstrates POST requests to create jobs, and GET requests to monitor job execution.
Category: Mapping, Addresses, Location, Logistics, Optimization, Postcodes, Transportation, Travel, Zip Codes

Description: The Zuppler Loyalty Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to return a list of all earning rules for a particular restaurant.
The Zuppler Carts Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to specify all actions related to order flow. They can all be accessed through REST endpoints or through Websocket.

The Zuppler Restaurants Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access restaurant data. This is a GraphQL endpoint to query Zuppler data. For the moment, Zuppler exposes channel, restaurant, item, and menus.
The Zuppler Orders Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to search for orders based on criteria. Search, create, and update orders.

The Zuppler Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement food and restaurant features. Zuppler uses an access token to allow access to the API. Register a new Zuppler account at the Zuppler Identity.
The Zuppler Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to authenticate the API. Developers can replace user and pass with their respective username and password.

The Slatwall Swift Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to create accounts, work with shopping carts, and place orders. The available collection of example scripts and endpoints connects and interacts with the Slatwall Commerce platform.

The Slatwall Python Sample Code demonstrates how to connect and interact with your Slatwall Commerce platform. Using the Slatwall API collection, create accounts, work with shopping carts, and place orders.
The Slatwall PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to authenticate, access an account, implement an eCommerce cart, and integrate eCommerce products.
The Slatwall Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API. Using the Slatwall API collection, create accounts, work with shopping carts, and place orders.

The Slatwall Java Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API. For ease of use inside Postman, store the API key in an environment variable called “Token” and this collection will automatically use it to make API calls.

The Slatwall Go Sample Code demonstrates how to create an API account with Go language. Before creating a specific API account or creating an API key, set the account to have API access to be part of the API permission group.
The Slatwall Products Curl Sample Code provides product-related endpoints. It demonstrates how to get a list of all the products.
The Slatwall Cart Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to retrieve information about the current cart (unplaced order) for the logged-in account.
The Slatwall Accounts Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to create/read/update/delete user accounts. With the sample code, retrieve information about the currently logged in account.

The Allmyles Booking Status Delivery Messages Objective-C Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement departure and arrival date, fare currency, refund amount, flight information, and final price amount.
The Allmyles Booking Status Delivery Messages Go Sample Code demonstrates how to make POST requests to the API. The response shows accurate results and errors when sending requests to the server.

The Allmyles Booking Status Delivery Messages Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement payment ID, ticket number, passenger name, form of payment, charged amount, flight status, invoice number, and final price amount.

The Allmyles Booking Status Delivery Messages PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement fare total, fare tax, expected price, fare currency, passenger type, payment ID, ticket number, passenger name, and form of payment.

The Allmyles Booking Status Delivery Messages Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement transaction dates, departure location, arrival location, transfer count, and operating carrier.
The Allmyles Booking Status Delivery Messages Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to make POST requests to access transaction dates, departure location, arrival location, and transfer count.

The Allmyles Booking Status Delivery Messages JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to use XMLHttpRequests with POST commands to access the API. Developers can get all response headers to implement the status of delivery messages.
The Allmyles Booking Status Delivery Messages Java Sample Code demonstrates how to access the status of delivery messages. In case of a new booking, Allmyles delivers all available data on creation.
JavaScript example that demonstrates how to retrieve files associated with a branch. Design branches work the same as version control branches.
This JavaScript example demonstrates how to perform membership data requests by querying the appropriate endpoint. This takes a user-id associated with the membership.
JavaScript example that demonstrates how to query for notification info by calling the specific endpoint. This requires a notification-id string.
This JavaScript example demonstrates how to retrieve organization data by querying the appropriate endpoint. This requires an org-id string.
This JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to retrieve reviews by querying the appropriate endpoint. This takes a file ID and is implemented asynchronously.
JavaScript example that demonstrates how to create an asynchronous request that passes organization ID numbers in order to retrieve review registers.
This JavaScript example demonstrates how to create a share link for design collaboration using an organization and project ID.
This JavaScript example demonstrates how to access the specified endpoint to retrieve membership lists and user lists.
This JavaScript example demonstrates how to build a GraphQL server connected to the Abstract platform. This is an Apollo server implementation.
This Python example demonstrates how to query a specified Devo endpoint after passing an API Key/Secret combination check. The response is transformed into JSON using the SIMPLECOMPACT_TO_OBJ module.
Python example that demonstrates how to search for a name to update line by line after configuring the SSL engine. This requires a sender key to query the endpoint.
This Python example demonstrates how to search for a name to delete line by line after configuring the SSL engine. This requires a sender key to query the endpoint.
This Python Sample Code configures the SSL engine, looks up a CSV file, and sends it to the specified endpoint.
This Python example demonstrates how to pack a message iterated 1000 times into a ZIP file. The test application sends this test file to the specified endpoint using a sender key.
This Python example demonstrates how to send a CSV file to the Devo servers after configuring the SSL engine.
Python Sample Code that requests eCommerce data within a specific date range. This transforms the data into JSON objects.
This Python example takes an API Key and Secret to create a client. The client queries for example CSV data.
The Allmyles Booking Status Delivery Messages Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to make requests for a new booking. Allmyles delivers all available data on creation.
The TryBooking JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to make calls to the API to receive booking data. Developers can implement into events, funding, and tickets applications.
The TryBooking Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to make requests. Responses include booking URL ID, fund transfer, balance, transactions, debit amount, and transaction date.
The TryBooking C# Sample Code demonstrates how to make requests to the API. Developers can use GET commands to perform calls and receive JSON formats in response.

The ProjectManager.com Retrieve Resources JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to use a resource instance that represents a resource created for a particular business account. This may be a resource associated with a particular user, or an inanimate resource.

The ProjectManager.com Retrieve Folders JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to implement a folder retrieval command that represents a directory created in ProjectManager.com. This may be a project folder or a user-created folder.

The ProjectManager.com Timesheets PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to add a timesheet entry for a particular day. It can only be one timesheet record per resource for a particular task or admin type for a specific date.

The ProjectManager.com Timesheets JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to implement a timesheet instance that records the number of hours spent on tasks and administrative activities/leave for a particular resource.
The ProjectManager.com Tasks PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to add task instances that represents a task created within a Project. It may be a high-level summary task or a task within a task.
Python example that demonstrates how to setup a transaction service. The test application creates a line item (product with SKU), and creates the transaction model.

Swift example that demonstrates how to create an application that lets people know when they have come into contact with someone who meets a set of criteria for a case of COVID-19. Criteria can be customized to determine if the risk is high enough to notify. Code is included to simulate server responses. This requires iOS 13.5+.

The ProjectManager.com Tasks JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate a task instance that represents a task created within a Project. It may be a high-level summary task or a task within a task.
The ProjectManager.com Projects jQuery Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to retrieve all the projects available to this user, in the order in which they were created.

The ProjectManager.com Projects PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to retrieve all the projects available to this user. There are no filters for this particular call, use /resources/{resourceId}/assignedProjects API to retrieve the projects assigned to a particular resource.
The ProjectManager.com PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API with key and GET requests. Print responses will display JSON formats.

The ProjectManager.com jQuery Sample Code demonstrates how to authenticate with an API key to be present, and it must be specified in the HTTP header of the request. Find the API key under the API tab on the Account page in ProjectManager.com.

This JavaScript example demonstrates how to send an asynchronous request to retrieve account details. This payer function is signed against a local node. After, transaction information is returned as JSON using the JSON.stringify() method.
JavaScript Sample Code that demonstrates how to send an asynchronous request to a locally hosted blockchain node, and retrieve transaction status. This returns JSON using the JSON.stringify() method.
This JavaScript Sample sends an asynchronous request to a locally hosted node, and retrieves the latest network block. This returns JSON using the JSON.stringify() method.
JavaScript Sample Code that demonstrates how to send a request to retrieve events by type and blocks. This is performed using a local node.
JavaScript example that demonstrates how to send an asynchronous request to retrieve account data. This returns a JavaScript object using the JSON.stringify() method.
Go Sample Code that demonstrates how to deploy a contract with an event defined, send a transaction that emits the event in the contract, and query for account creation events and custom events.
Go Sample Code that demonstrates how to deploy a contract locally using an emulator. This generates an account creation script, and deploys the contract using a Non-fungible Token.

Go Sample Code that demonstrates how to generate a random key, create an account and associate it with the key, create a transaction and let the root account sign it, and send the transaction to the network.

This Go example illustrates how to create a new key, add it to an account, create a transaction, and sign the transaction with the new account. After this process is complete, the transaction is sent to the blockchain.
This Swift Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate an user interface with an HTTP client, authenticate against a base URL, and retrieve the client's version.
Java example that demonstrates how to initialize a client and use an API Key and API Secret combination to authenticate properly. This performs a GET request after.
This Android example is a basic implementation of a client capable of receiving messages.

.NET Sample Code that demonstrates how to initiate a transaction. The test application takes an API Key, creates a client associated with a Client ID, initializes a TSS payload, and starts a transaction.

The Guestmeter Property Guest List Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to get a guest list of a property. There are no request parameters for this method. Must be a GET request with a JSON-formatted list of the parameters as the request body.

The Guestmeter Guest Rating Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to obtain a guest rating details by guestID parameter. Must be a GET request with a JSON-formatted list of the parameters as the request body.

The Guestmeter Satisfaction Survey Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to send a guest satisfaction survey via SMS or Email. Must be a POST request with a JSON-formatted list of the parameters as the request body.
The TrueAccord Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to authenticate to the TrueAccord API by providing an API key as a username using HTTP Basic Authentication. The password part is ignored.
The Kintone iOS Sample Code as a reference presents how to install CocoaPods or Carthage. This is a Swift-tailored experience to integrate an app with Kintone.
The Kintone JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to retrieve records of an app. API token authentication is required.
The Signiant Jet Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to generate an OAuth token by using the cURL utility to call the /oauth/token endpoint. Code also allows creating a storage profile.
JavaScript example that demonstrates how to sign blocks of a blockchain network during the transaction writing process. This uses the BlockSigner artifact.
This JavaScript example demonstrates how to catch exceptions during random Secret Key generation.
JavaScript example that demonstrates how to validate using arbitrary-precision decimal and non-decimal arithmetic during candidate voting.
The Travefy Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to make requests to the API to implement itinerary, planning, and scheduling features into travel applications. Postmal collection available.

The Travefy Python Sample Code demonstrates how to use either an http client or requests to access the API. Developers can use the resources available that include versioning, environments, and authentication.
The Travefy Objective-C Sample Code provides cURL, HTTP request 2, and pecl http as alternatives to access the API. Developers can make their first call by accessing with an API Key.
The Travefy Objective-C Sample Code demonstrates how to use the resources available to create a travel itinerary application: environments, versioning, changelog, single sign-on, and API pricing.
The Travefy JavaScript Sample Code offers three methods to access the API with JavaScript: fetch, jQuery, and XHR. Travefy provides an Ope API with Postman collection.
The Travefy Java Sample Code provides OkHttp and Unirest code to access the API. Developers can implement travel features including itinerary, planning, and scheduling into applications.
The Travefy Go Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement a traveler itinerary into websites and applications. Developers can integrate planning and scheduling for traveler clients.
The ScrapingBee Java Sample Code demonstrates how to create a classic request, fetch a request and return content, and print content.
The ScrapingBee Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to perform data mining and web scraping. ScrapingBee handles headless browsers and rotates proxies.

The MeiliSearch Documents Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to search for documents in command line and using the web interface. The search engine is now aware of documents and can serve those via an HTTP server. The web interface allows testing MeiliSearch interactively.
The MeiliSearch Index Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to create an index. Developers can use a movie database as a sample dataset, also available in the datasets/ directory.
Ruby example that demonstrates how to implement subscription-based event notifications associated with user outbound/inbound messaging.
Category: Cloud, Analytics, Browsers, Mobile, Video, Voice, WebRTC

Description: This NodeJS example demonstrates how to implement real-time SMS events including inbound messages, outbound messages, and notifications. Also, this demonstrates how to perform user SMS messaging.
Category: Cloud, Analytics, Browsers, Mobile, Video, Voice, WebRTC

Description: Python Sample Code that demonstrates how to implement real-time SMS events, and user SMS messaging.
Category: Cloud, Analytics, Browsers, Mobile, Video, Voice, WebRTC

Description: This PHP Sample Code is a simple SMS application which allows for user SMS messaging, and subscriptions.
Category: Cloud, Analytics, Browsers, Mobile, Video, Voice, WebRTC

Description: The Travefy C# Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement itinerary into traveler clients applications. Pre-made requests are available to explore the API using Postman.
The Travefy Curl Sample Code demonstrates how developers can add the API to implement itinerary, schedule, and planning features into travel systems.
The True Social Metrics Trend Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access trends. Developers can receive trend reports for a selected date range.
The True Social Metrics Metric Source Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access metrics. Developers can receive metrics for a selected date range.
The True Social Metrics Source Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access a source. Developers can get information about sources for custom accounts.
The True Social Metrics Account Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access an account list. Developers can get information about accessible accounts.
PHP example that demonstrates how to send a fax, how to resend a fax, how to query for a fax's status, and how to create a new outbound fax register.
PHP Sample Code that demonstrates how to handle inbound faxes. This example retrieves the path, and queries the API.
NodeJS example that demonstrates how to send a large file. This sends the file in 500 byte chunks, and monitors its progress.
NodeJS example that demonstrates how to send multiple files. As an example, this sends PDF and HTML documents as compatible files.
NodeJS example that demonstrates how to retrieve all recent faxes. This also cancels all currently processing faxes.
NodeJS Sample Code that demonstrates how to check the status of a fax. This uses a faxId variable.
NodeJS example that demonstrates how to send a single fax by providing a number and a compatible file.
The Flock Vision Plans Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate vision plans into human resources solutions. Attributes and arguments are similar to Medical Plan endpoints.
The Flock Dental Plans Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to implement dental plans into a human resources system. Attributes and arguments are similar to Medical Plan endpoints.
The Flock Medical Plans Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to return a collection of all medical plans for a given company.
The Checkbook.io Invoice Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to create a new invoice with an account, amount, attachments, description, name, number, and recipient.

The Checkbook.io Paper Check Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to create a digital check to send a payment. In order to be able to send checks, users need to have a verified bank account in the system.

The Checkbook.io Digital Checks Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to integrate digital checks into applications. A verified bank account is required. Developers can refer to the Add a Bank Account section for instructions.

The FireText Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to use an API Key to authenticate the API, send a test message, and receive a response in JSON format. FireText provides messaging services that enhance text and marketing campaigns in England.
The QuadPay Mobile Token-Based iOS Sample Code demonstrates how to start a QuadPay checkout in an iOS app and how to initialize the QuadPay SDK.

The User.com Web Push Python Sample Code demonstrates how to get a single web push campaign. The response shows name, messages, recipients, category, statistics, delivery, received, scheduled, and clicked.
The User.com Email PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to send messages. Developers can send email messages using the API. To do so, set subject, content, and receivers for the message.
The User.com Conversation Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to get a single conversation. Developers can get information about a single channel via a simple GET request.

The User.com Products JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to create a product category. Developers can group users with lists, this will allow to easily send email campaigns to a certain group of users, or filter them using Lists attribute.
The User.com Phone Campaign jQuery Sample Code demonstrates how to create a new phone campaign with HTTP POST request.
The User.com CRM Company Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to create a new company with an HTTP POST request.
.NET example that highlights the process of how to use DocuVieware through the PassportPDF REST API to visualize documents.
This Kotlin Sample Code simulates signature handling, initiates a payment, and handles the payment result.
Kotlin example that creates an instance, retrieves a Token, retrieves the selected environment, and creates a SHA-256 hash to implement signing.
Kotlin example that implements customized payment displays in Android. This displays a payment button in an application with 2 different options.
This Cordova example serves as a template for building iOS and Android payment processing solutions connected to Sonect.
JavaScript example that demonstrates how to designate a maximum cap when creating Ethereum Token supply.
This JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to test if Token burning works as intended. Token burning increases token value because it decreases total supply.
The Docamatic Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API with an npm. Developers can make bearer token requests to the API and access JSON body, source of news, formats, and media types.
The Docamatic Laravel Sample Code demonstrates how to use a token to authenticate the API. Developers can use a source, format, and media to access documentation features from the API.

JavaScript example that demonstrates Ethereum ERC-20 Token tests. This application asserts that the implementation can set decimals during construction, emit approval events, and modify allowances in non-zero accounts.
The Docamatic PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to use a bearer API Key to access the API. It includes JSON formats to make calls to the interface.

The Docamatic Python Sample Code demonstrates how to install pip into the right OS to make requests to the API. Developers can access data from a source of news, including a format, and selecting a media.
The Docamatic Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement document features into applications. Requirements include NET HTTP, a URI, and JSON format.
The Docamatic Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API with an API Key. Developers can implement content type from a given source to implement into websites.
JavaScript Sample Code that demonstrates how to implement asynchronous, signed SafeMath operations. This tests if overflow occurs for positive and negative values.
The Sellbrite Curl Sample Code provides a cURL request using basic authentication. API information includes carrier names and shipping carriers and methods.
This JavaScript example demonstrates how to perform SafeMath operations in Solidity. This is used to support UINT (32-bit unsigned integer) values and prevent overflow.
JavaScript example that demonstrates how to implement an Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm as an asynchronous function in smart contract projects.
This JavaScript example demonstrates how to use OpenZeppelin instead of Ethereum truffle migrations using CLI JavaScript. This is used to deploy upgradeable instances.
JavaScript example that demonstrates how to link an Ethereum package to a project. This deploys an upgradeable ERC-20 using @openzeppelin/contracts-ethereum-package.
JavaScript example that demonstrates how to use the OpenZeppelin create2 command for deployment tasks. This is performed using the JavaScript interface and the Command-Line Interface.

The User.com Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to make a request that will display a list of users. The response pagination shows up to 50 results per page to prevent overload of data and slowing down an app.

The Contify Locations Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access a list of locations by interacting with the API. Each location in the search result will contain an Id value along with additional information like the location name and location type.
The Contify Locations Shell Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to return a list of locations. The list can be searched by using the Name or Type parameters.
The Contify Content Source Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement intelligence features into marketing websites and platforms as a service.
The Contify Content Source Shell Sample Code demonstrates how to access content's source name, domain URL, and global rank for each source.
The Contify Company Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement intelligence features. App ID and app secret are valid to authenticate and make requests to the API.
The Contify Company Shell Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API to implement intelligence features into marketing applications. The sample supports JSON structured commands.
This Go example implements a way of restarting code workflows in case of bad code changes. This restarts all outstanding TripWorkflow executions, and replays all signals from the previous run.
Go example that demonstrates the invocation of workflows and activities using name rather than a strongly typed function.
This Go Sample Code highlights a DSL workflow implementation. The given YAML files define a custom workflow and is processed by this example.

Go example that demonstrates how to add context propagation to an application's workflow. The context propagator extracts and passes on information present in the context.Context and workflow.Context objects across the workflow.
This Go example highlights cron job scheduling based on a given schedule specification. This serves as a simple scheduler, but more complicated logic can be implemented.
Go Sample Code that demonstrates how to add a multi-choice workflow. Different branches are added depending on the activity.
This Go example highlights the logic required to cancel activity workflows. When a workflow is canceled, it has to get a new disconnected context.
Go example that demonstrates how to execute multiple branches in parallel. The number of branches is controlled by passing a parameter. This requires a Temporal service running.
The Precognitive JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to use the JavaScript API and how to use a JavaScript tag to set values assigned to the Decisioning API.
The DEAR Systems Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to make a call with GET requests. Developers can use an application Key to authenticate.

The DEAR Systems PHP Sample Code demonstrates how to connect to the API. DEAR Inventory API is part of DEAR Inventory web application at <a href="https://inventory.dearsystems.com">https://inventory.dearsystems.com
The VTEX SKU Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to retrieve the IDs of all SKUs (stock keeping units) of the product labels in the store. Presents the result with page size and pagination.

The VTEX Category and Brand Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to make GET requests to access a catalog system with category levels. Developers can make requests that will display JSON formats in return.

Python Sample Code that demonstrates how to perform radiotherapy structural data tests. The application verifies that downloading a specific file and modifying a radiotherapy structure works correctly.
This Python example demonstrates how to attach a task query to a pre-generated patient. This application adds dose composition details as a test.
Python example that demonstrates how to retrieve images from ProKnow and download them to the specified directory.
This Python example creates a test patient and associates doses with them. The application retrieves dose analytics, generates a patient, and adds metrics.
.NET Sample Code that demonstrates how to create a computed metric, add objectives to said metric, and create a scoreboard containing said metrics.
.NET example that demonstrates how to read several metrics after deserializing a JSON file.
This .NET example demonstrates document-related operations. The application creates a file, waits until processing finishes, and uploads a file.
.NET Sample Code that demonstrates how to associate a patient with a collection. The application retrieves a patient's summary asynchronously.

This .NET example initializes the SDK, deletes an existing collection, creates a workspace, creates a patient, and creates a new collection. Also, this test application verifies that the collection changes were saved.
The Easyship JavaScript Sample Code demonstrates how to use an XML HTTP request to access the API. Developers can then use POST commands to receive JSON formats as responses.
The Easyship Python Sample Code demonstrates how to access the API with POST requests. The API will return JSON formats as responses.
The Easyship Ruby Sample Code demonstrates how to use URI, NET/HTTP and Open SSL as requirements to access the Rates API. Developers need a to paste a bearer token to authenticate.
The Easyship Node.js Sample Code demonstrates how to make requests to the API with POST commands. Bearer token authorization is required.
The Easyship Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to access the Rates API that allows requesting a list of shipping quotes for a prospective Shipment.
The Onederful Eligibility and Benefits Curl Sample Code shows subscriber, dependents, patient, providers, dental plans, deductible, coinsurance, co payment, out of pocket, and disclaimers.
The Onederful Payer List Curl Sample Code provides ID and name of parameters that can include abbreviations and names of dental insurance companies.

The Benzinga Python Sample Code provides a sample test financial module and sample test news data modules. Financial data methods include charts, quotes, dividends, ratings, earnings, economics, guidance, IPO, conference calls, and valuation ratios.

The Experitest Curl Sample Code demonstrates how developers can use cURL to access the API. As this request is written, it can contain both headers and body parameters. Header parameters usually are transmitted in CURL commands with -H parameter and body parameters are transmitted with -F parameter.

The Experitest Java Sample Code provides a Gradle dependency and a code dependency to get the application. Resources developers need to add include a user name, password, access key, project name, and project ID.
Java example that demonstrates how to copy an initialized collection, unload datasets, remove members from a collection, and unload collections.
This C++ example demonstrates how to create a client session, and perform a query for a microscopy image.
C++ example that demonstrates how to create and initialize empty collections. After copying the original collection, datasets can be unloaded.

This NodeJS Sample Code demonstrates that resource-related endpoints return valid information. This example highlights the process of making a bot retrieve resources, perform resource endpoint requests, and send texts directly.
This NodeJS Sample Code asserts that the chat bot can ingest chat payloads in different situations. The test application creates a chat room based on the provided contact.
This NodeJS Sample Code demonstrates callback-based conversation creation, and promise-based conversation creation.
This NodeJS example demonstrates context-related bot messaging for favorite foods, and naming.
This NodeJS Sample Code performs bot-related events. The application registers a callback, sends a message, and initializes bot log activities.
This NodeJS example demonstrates how to make bots send messages through middlewares.
The Syncro Curl Sample Code demonstrates how to use Swagger. When developers make a successful request, Syncro will produce a curl that can be used to get the same response seen in Swagger.
NodeJS example that demonstrates how to make a bot to send random messages with delay, asynchronous messages, and sequential messages.
This NodeJS example highlights the process required to initialize a bot and send a message to a specific user before leaving the conversation.
NodeJS Sample Code that demonstrates how to manage chat bot state message actions.
NodeJS example that demonstrates how to implement event-based triggers. The application starts a trigger after review, and on results.

The Redash Python Sample Code demonstrates how to use manage a Redash instance. Still, a work in progress, the wrapper allows polling for query results, refreshing a dashboard, and exporting all queries as files.

This JavaScript Sample Code are example applications that illustrate how to use a Bitcoin Cash app for the FullStack.cash BCH JavaScript library and REST API. It shows you how to; create a wallet, send BCH, create SLP tokens, read and write text to the blockchain, and more. FullStack.cash provides services for applications to interact with the Bitcoin Cash Blockchain.
This TypeScript example highlights how to test registration-related actions. The application creates an identity asynchronously, and displays an exception in case of error.

TypeScript Sample Code that demonstrates how to test notification management services. The application creates an info notification, schedules a notification, and removes a notification using invokeDismiss.
TypeScript example that highlights how to test if the navigation method extracts the route name and parameters from the URL correctly.
TypeScript example that highlights how to test account-related actions. The application creates a store, handles encrypted seeds, and retrieves account claims.
TypeScript example that demonstrates how to envelop sensitive identity information in a JSON object.
This TypeScript example highlights how to transform into and from JSON objects. Documents with signature details are enveloped around a JSON object.
